<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06194243 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06194243 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: Strauss  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  LAW; PROFESSIONAL; WASHINGTON-DC; POLITICS  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  If he's confirmed as the new ambassador to Moscow, Robert Strauss will forgohundreds of thousands of dollars he now gets as a director of severalcompanies. But he'll collect $1.4 million from his law firm.;    &quot;When I leavethis firm, I leave permanently,&quot; Strauss, 73, said. &quot;My name is out of thefirm.&quot;  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  STRAUSS WOULD QUIT LAW FIRM  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Strauss' financial disclosure forms, released Thursday, show he wouldreceive the money for selling his senior partnership in Akin, Gump, Strauss,Hauer andamp; Feld -- the powerhouse law firm he founded in 1945 after working as anFBI special agent.;    Strauss also has promised to resign all his corporatedirectorships and put his millions of dollars of assets into a blind trust.;   Ambassadors, like other presidential appointees, are required by law todivest any financial interests that are likely to conflict with their newposition.;    President Bush nominated Strauss, a lawyer and lobbyist andformer Democratic Party chairman, as ambassador to the Soviet Union lastmonth. The Senate is expected to approve the choice.;    Strauss left AkinGump in the 1970s to take the Democratic post and later to serve as U.S. traderepresentative and special Middle East envoy under President Carter. Herejoined the firm in 1980.;    &quot;As a former government official, I amparticularly sensitive to the need to avoid even the appearance of using mypublic office for private gain or showing improper preference to one privateparty over another,&quot; Strauss wrote in a July 5 letter to the StateDepartment's legal adviser.;    Strauss also said he intends to sell more than$1.5 million in shares of Archer Daniels Midland Co. and Pepsico Inc. owned byhim and his wife, Helen, within 90 days of being sworn in as ambassador toMoscow.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Washington  </CITY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910712  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  July  </MONTH><PG.COL>  21A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  291  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday July 12, 199100194243,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>